SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT

1. Definitions

    "Licensee": Any individual or entity using the Software within the United States.

    "Individual": A natural person not acting on behalf of a business entity.

    "Corporation": Any business entity (e.g., LLC, corporation, partnership) organized under U.S. or state law.

    "Employees": Full-time, part-time (calculated as full-time equivalents [FTEs] per IRS guidelines), and contractors directly engaged in the Corporation’s operations.

    "Software": The software product, including updates, governed by this license.

    "Modification": Any alteration, adaptation, or derivative work under 17 U.S.C. § 101 (U.S. Copyright Act).

    "Redistribution": Distribution, sale, or transfer of the Software to third parties, including via SaaS or cloud platforms.

2. Grant of License

    2.1 Free Use License:

        Eligibility: Individuals and Corporations with ≤25 Employees (calculated as FTEs) may use the Software at no cost.

        Scope: Non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the Software as provided for internal purposes only.

        Restrictions:

            No Modification: Reverse-engineering, decompiling, or creating derivative works is prohibited (per 17 U.S.C. § 1201, DMCA anti-circumvention).

            No Redistribution: The Software may not be resold, relicensed, or bundled with other products.

    2.2 Paid License:

        Corporations with >25 Employees must contact Licensor to negotiate a paid license. Fees will comply with U.S. tax and commercial law.

3. Compliance & Certification (U.S.-Specific)

    Employee Verification: Corporations must submit annual certification of employee count (including FTEs and contractors) via signed affidavit.

    Audit Rights: Licensor may request reasonable documentation (e.g., payroll records, IRS filings) to verify compliance.

    Growth Transition: If a Corporation exceeds 25 Employees, it must notify Licensor within 30 days and transition to a Paid License within 60 days.

4. Termination

    Immediate Termination: Unauthorized use, Modification, or Redistribution voids this license. Licensor may terminate access without notice.

    Post-Termination: Licensee must delete all Software copies and certify destruction in writing.

5. Disclaimer of Warranty (As-Is Basis)
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED “AS IS” WITHOUT WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED UNDER THE UNIFORM COMMERCIAL CODE (UCC) AND STATE LAW.

6. Limitation of Liability
LICENSOR IS NOT LIABLE FOR DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES UNDER THIS AGREEMENT, EXCEPT WHERE PROHIBITED BY STATE LAW (E.G., CALIFORNIA CIVIL CODE § 1668).

7. Governing Law & Dispute Resolution

    Jurisdiction: This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of South Carolina and applicable U.S. federal law.

    Venue: Disputes will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in South Carolina.

8. Severability
If any term is unenforceable under U.S. or state law, the remaining terms remain valid.

9. Entire Agreement
This document supersedes all prior agreements. Amendments require written consent.
